  "title": "Site Engineering",
  "description": "<p><strong>Full Job Description</strong></p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Plan, lead and monitor progress and performance against the project plan</li><li>Manages day-to-day operational aspects of a project, which includes manpower planning, construction progress monitoring, preparation of master schedule and cost control</li><li>Take actions to deal with the results of delay, bad weather or emergencies at construction site</li><li>Liaise with clients, consultants, subcontractors and authorities in resolving site issues</li><li>Effectively applies safe and economical methodology enforces project standards</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><p>·       Recognized Degree in Civil Engineering or its equivalent</p><p>·       Minimum 8 years' construction experience in project/site management in construction industry</p><p>·       Independent, diligent, meticulous and highly motivated with excellent team spirit</p>",
